9
00:00:28,990 --> 00:00:31,792
   

10
00:00:43,208 --> 00:00:44,722
Mister!

11
00:00:44,722 --> 00:00:46,685
Mr. Homeless!

12
00:00:48,855 --> 00:00:51,364
What are you doing? Let's go inside.

13
00:01:26,701 --> 00:01:28,160
Dry yourself.

14
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:32,501
You said you hated the rain, so why did you let yourself get soaked?

15
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:41,134
 Madam! 

16
00:01:43,193 --> 00:01:44,971
 Excuse me... 

17
00:01:49,589 --> 00:01:54,528
 The one who was with the madam right before the accident was him. 

18
00:01:57,523 --> 00:02:00,131
 Madam! Wake up! 

19
00:02:00,131 --> 00:02:01,730
 Madam! 

20
00:02:05,187 --> 00:02:06,988
 Help! 

21
00:02:07,999 --> 00:02:10,172
 She is dying! 

22
00:02:10,172 --> 00:02:12,482
 Please, someone help! 

23
00:02:16,903 --> 00:02:22,137
 If he was there at the time of the madam's accident... 

24
00:02:23,430 --> 00:02:26,262
 Perhaps her accident was... 

25
00:02:26,262 --> 00:02:29,965
You really are a handful.

26
00:02:29,965 --> 00:02:33,561
If you fall sick, I'll be the one to suffer.

27
00:02:33,561 --> 00:02:35,436
Stop, young lady!

28
00:02:35,436 --> 00:02:37,853
I was in the middle of something important,

29
00:02:37,853 --> 00:02:39,828
and you interrupted my train of thought.

30
00:02:39,828 --> 00:02:41,967
What were you thinking about?

31
00:02:41,967 --> 00:02:43,790
The madam's...

32
00:02:46,249 --> 00:02:47,379
Never mind.

33
00:02:47,379 --> 00:02:50,811
Why stop mid-sentence? Don't leave me hanging.

34
00:02:50,811 --> 00:02:52,698
What is it?

35
00:02:56,105 --> 00:02:59,958
I am not sure if I should tell you this first.

36
00:02:59,958 --> 00:03:01,786
But I think...

37
00:03:10,578 --> 00:03:13,416
Go get changed now!

38
00:03:26,370 --> 00:03:28,170
Did he...

39
00:03:29,231 --> 00:03:31,700
really see me?

40
00:04:08,121 --> 00:04:09,657
 Madam! 

41
00:04:15,087 --> 00:04:16,351
 Madam! Wake up! 

42
00:04:16,351 --> 00:04:18,003
 Madam! 

43
00:04:19,603 --> 00:04:21,485
 Help! 

44
00:04:21,485 --> 00:04:23,699
 Is anyone around? 

45
00:04:24,328 --> 00:04:26,527
 She is dying! 

46
00:04:26,527 --> 00:04:28,546
 Please, someone help! 

47
00:04:28,546 --> 00:04:30,136
 Madam! 

48
00:04:30,136 --> 00:04:32,101
 Madam, get up! 

49
00:04:33,457 --> 00:04:35,994
 Madam, wake up! 

50
00:04:37,794 --> 00:04:39,357
 Madam! 

51
00:04:41,063 --> 00:04:43,278
 How could this happen? 

52
00:04:44,772 --> 00:04:46,936
How much did he see?

53
00:05:10,468 --> 00:05:12,233
What is the matter?

54
00:05:13,464 --> 00:05:16,316
The jar my mom cherished...

55
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:18,425
Why is it broken?

56
00:05:19,247 --> 00:05:21,478
Did you do this?

57
00:05:22,758 --> 00:05:25,120
I was out with you and just got back.

58
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:27,529
When would I have had the time?

59
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:50,141
Someone has been rummaging through the kitchen.

60
00:05:51,116 --> 00:05:52,829
A thief?

61
00:06:25,878 --> 00:06:29,760
Other than the broken jar, is anything missing?

62
00:06:29,760 --> 00:06:31,225
I don't think so.

63
00:06:31,225 --> 00:06:33,761
The cash at the counter is untouched,

64
00:06:33,761 --> 00:06:36,213
and all the ingredients are still here, right?

65
00:06:36,213 --> 00:06:37,799
That is right.

66
00:06:37,799 --> 00:06:41,464
But someone definitely went through the kitchen.

67
00:06:41,464 --> 00:06:43,045
Really?

68
00:06:43,741 --> 00:06:48,694
By any chance, do you know how much that broken jar is worth?

69
00:06:48,694 --> 00:06:50,730
I'm not sure.

70
00:06:50,730 --> 00:06:55,081
My mom treasured it so much she wouldn't even let me touch it.

71
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:57,256
I'll file a report for now.

72
00:06:57,256 --> 00:07:01,272
Check again for any other missing items and let me know.

73
00:07:02,356 --> 00:07:04,347
Thank you, detective.

74
00:07:04,347 --> 00:07:07,156
You've been through a lot. Would you like a cup of coffee?

75
00:07:07,156 --> 00:07:08,821
No, I'm good.

76
00:07:08,821 --> 00:07:10,911
I no longer drink coffee.

77
00:07:11,673 --> 00:07:12,916
Then maybe the others...

78
00:07:12,916 --> 00:07:15,479
No.

79
00:07:15,479 --> 00:07:18,569
They all quit, too.

80
00:07:18,569 --> 00:07:22,341
I'll go upstairs and check if anything else is missing.

81
00:07:27,231 --> 00:07:29,347
You got all the fingerprints, right?

82
00:07:29,347 --> 00:07:31,294
- Yes, sir. 
 - Okay.

83
00:07:32,666 --> 00:07:35,277
- Goodnight. 
 - Excuse me!

84
00:07:37,109 --> 00:07:39,637
What is it this time?

85
00:07:40,495 --> 00:07:44,864
Are you trying to drag up the past and start another argument?

86
00:07:46,545 --> 00:07:50,041
I have something important to tell you.

87
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:53,058
What could possibly be so important?

88
00:07:53,058 --> 00:07:55,475
Why are you acting so seriously?

89
00:07:55,475 --> 00:07:57,783
It is about the madam.

90
00:07:59,609 --> 00:08:01,621
Not that again.

91
00:08:01,621 --> 00:08:04,688
I told you, she was alone that day.

92
00:08:04,688 --> 00:08:08,563
No, she was not alone that day.

93
00:08:09,327 --> 00:08:13,124
She had company, and I think I know who it was.

94
00:08:46,897 --> 00:08:51,119
You said you didn't see the person's face.

95
00:08:51,119 --> 00:08:53,027
That is right.

96
00:08:53,027 --> 00:08:56,832
But I remember everything else,

97
00:08:58,495 --> 00:09:01,806
and I have found someone who matches.

98
00:09:02,752 --> 00:09:04,809
Come on.

99
00:09:04,809 --> 00:09:08,121
Without the face, it could be anyone.

100
00:09:08,121 --> 00:09:10,378
How can you identify someone just by their body shape?

101
00:09:10,378 --> 00:09:14,486
Do not underestimate the memory of the Transcendent Genius.

102
00:09:16,289 --> 00:09:18,117
I am certain.

103
00:09:18,117 --> 00:09:19,794
It was him.

104
00:09:19,794 --> 00:09:22,494
Do you have any proof?

105
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:30,623
   

106
00:09:37,162 --> 00:09:39,033
The evidence I have

107
00:09:40,193 --> 00:09:42,464
is what I saw and heard.

108
00:09:42,997 --> 00:09:45,412
So I need your help.

109
00:09:45,412 --> 00:09:47,823
Please investigate him thoroughly.

110
00:09:47,823 --> 00:09:51,001
Find out why he met the madam just before the accident

111
00:09:51,001 --> 00:09:54,230
and what exactly happened on those stairs that day...

112
00:09:54,230 --> 00:09:56,517
What did you just say?

113
00:10:00,813 --> 00:10:04,634
Who did my mom meet just before the accident?

114
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:09,318
Well, that is...

115
00:10:15,823 --> 00:10:19,321
I asked you a question. Who was the person my mom met?

116
00:10:38,596 --> 00:10:41,744
This has gotten out of hand.

117
00:10:41,744 --> 00:10:43,603
What should we do?

118
00:10:44,302 --> 00:10:45,551
What else?

119
00:10:45,551 --> 00:10:48,389
Detective Kang, you need to contain it again.

120
00:10:51,118 --> 00:10:54,820
A witness has come forward, and the victim's family will take action.

121
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:57,284
What exactly do you expect me to do?

122
00:10:57,284 --> 00:10:59,000
Believe it or not, I'm a cop.

123
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:02,100
I can't ignore procedures

124
00:11:02,109 --> 00:11:04,998
and keep covering for you.

125
00:11:04,998 --> 00:11:08,419
But you've been doing exactly that all this time.

126
00:11:08,419 --> 00:11:10,565
And willingly, at that.

127
00:11:12,897 --> 00:11:17,667
There's only so much I can sweep under the rug.

128
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:20,300
Now that it's come to this,

129
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:24,610
I have no choice but to investigate you.

130
00:11:24,613 --> 00:11:30,241
Investigate me based on the words of someone with no clear identity?

131
00:11:32,622 --> 00:11:36,620
Even if we ignore him, what about Bong Eun Sil?

132
00:11:36,620 --> 00:11:40,373
You really think the victim's daughter will just let this go?

133
00:11:40,373 --> 00:11:44,888
So, you're saying she's suspecting me just because of what he said.

134
00:11:44,888 --> 00:11:48,435
Then, all we need to do is invalidate what she heard.

135
00:11:49,006 --> 00:11:53,244
How do we invalidate something that she has already heard?

136
00:11:53,244 --> 00:11:56,064
Try to make some sense.

137
00:12:13,689 --> 00:12:15,402
Eun Sil.

138
00:12:15,402 --> 00:12:18,556
I figured you'd come, so I waited.

139
00:12:19,508 --> 00:12:22,536
You should've called me instead of waiting outside in the cold.

140
00:12:22,536 --> 00:12:25,214
This isn't something to talk about over the phone.

141
00:12:26,238 --> 00:12:28,120
Let's go inside.

142
00:12:38,187 --> 00:12:40,741
Thank you so much for earlier.

143
00:12:40,741 --> 00:12:43,354
I was caught off guard when it suddenly started raining.

144
00:12:47,071 --> 00:12:50,207
I'll buy you a new umbrella.

145
00:12:51,219 --> 00:12:55,568
I left yours in front of the restaurant, but I can't find it anymore.

146
00:12:56,840 --> 00:13:00,298
That's not what I'm here for.

147
00:13:05,364 --> 00:13:10,023
Chef, I heard you met my mom.

148
00:13:10,656 --> 00:13:13,202
Just before her accident.

149
00:13:16,322 --> 00:13:18,238
That's true.

150
00:13:18,238 --> 00:13:22,219
I saw her that morning, just before dawn.

151
00:13:22,219 --> 00:13:24,594
Then why didn't you tell me?

152
00:13:24,594 --> 00:13:26,348
I wanted to.

153
00:13:26,348 --> 00:13:29,278
I wanted to tell you so many times, but...

154
00:13:31,792 --> 00:13:35,623
Every time I tried, that person was there.

155
00:13:35,623 --> 00:13:38,258
That person? Who?

156
00:13:40,063 --> 00:13:42,564
Oh, do you mean Mr. Homeless?

157
00:13:44,341 --> 00:13:49,905
I assume he's the one who told you that I met your mother.

158
00:13:51,237 --> 00:13:54,266
Yes, that's right.

159
00:13:55,606 --> 00:13:58,094
He's keeping me in check.

160
00:13:59,894 --> 00:14:03,518
Why would he do that?

161
00:14:04,297 --> 00:14:07,522
Because he's afraid of the truth I know.

162
00:14:08,350 --> 00:14:12,315
He wanted to make sure you wouldn't trust me.

163
00:14:19,719 --> 00:14:24,112
What is taking her so long?

164
00:14:36,332 --> 00:14:39,836
   

165
00:14:48,738 --> 00:14:50,190
 The recipient is unavailable. 

166
00:14:50,190 --> 00:14:52,480
 Please leave a message after the beep. 

167
00:14:52,489 --> 00:14:54,900
 A service charge may apply. 

168
00:14:57,312 --> 00:14:59,717
Who is speaking?

169
00:14:59,717 --> 00:15:02,310
Where is Lady Eun Sil?

170
00:15:02,310 --> 00:15:04,740
Call her here at once!

171
00:15:04,740 --> 00:15:05,919
Excuse me?

172
00:15:05,919 --> 00:15:09,965
   

173
00:15:15,193 --> 00:15:16,604
Go on.

174
00:15:16,604 --> 00:15:21,929
The truth is... your mother called for me that night.

175
00:15:21,929 --> 00:15:25,045
She said she had something important to discuss.

176
00:15:26,390 --> 00:15:28,563
At that hour?

177
00:15:29,267 --> 00:15:34,498
She seemed restless, unable to sleep, and for good reason.

178
00:15:36,055 --> 00:15:38,897
She told me she had been scammed.

179
00:15:38,897 --> 00:15:42,471
My mom... was scammed?

180
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:44,717
Yes.

181
00:15:45,657 --> 00:15:49,604
By the man you're working with now.

182
00:15:50,376 --> 00:15:52,968
It was Gyosan.

183
00:15:53,807 --> 00:15:55,831
What?

184
00:15:55,831 --> 00:15:58,105
Mr. Homeless?

185
00:16:00,428 --> 00:16:02,664
Chef, what are you trying to say?

186
00:16:02,664 --> 00:16:05,883
That man isn't the type to do something like that.

187
00:16:05,883 --> 00:16:07,721
Then...

188
00:16:08,342 --> 00:16:12,278
Do I look like someone who would lie to you?

189
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:16,688
That's not what I meant...

190
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:20,330
He barely even knows how the world works.

191
00:16:20,330 --> 00:16:22,430
What kind of scam could he pull?

192
00:16:22,431 --> 00:16:25,094
That naivety is exactly what deceived your mother.

193
00:16:25,094 --> 00:16:29,615
That night, she told me

194
00:16:29,615 --> 00:16:32,793
she had helped him out of pity...

195
00:16:32,793 --> 00:16:35,287
Only to have him stab her in the back.

196
00:16:38,492 --> 00:16:43,523
Now, do you understand why I never trusted him?

197
00:16:44,721 --> 00:16:49,856
I've been trying to warn you all along.

198
00:16:51,520 --> 00:16:54,029
You must be mistaken.

199
00:16:55,236 --> 00:17:00,061
- The Mr. Homeless I know... 
 - And what exactly do you know about him?

200
00:17:02,404 --> 00:17:05,586
- Well... 
 - That he came from Joseon?

201
00:17:06,443 --> 00:17:09,610
That a man who supposedly never cooked before

202
00:17:09,610 --> 00:17:13,180
can suddenly make quality dishes overnight?

203
00:17:13,184 --> 00:17:15,752
All those ridiculous lies.

204
00:17:17,120 --> 00:17:19,071
How could you...

205
00:17:19,996 --> 00:17:23,013
possibly believe them?

206
00:17:23,013 --> 00:17:25,716
It wasn't his words I believed.

207
00:17:26,613 --> 00:17:30,184
I believed in the character he revealed through his actions.

208
00:17:30,184 --> 00:17:32,219
His character.

209
00:17:32,219 --> 00:17:35,836
Sure, your mother must have thought the same.

210
00:17:35,836 --> 00:17:39,594
And yet, she was deceived and came to me.

211
00:17:41,679 --> 00:17:47,075
That day, your mother and I met for a brief moment.

212
00:17:48,926 --> 00:17:50,902
And I...

213
00:17:50,902 --> 00:17:53,754
I regret that more than anything.

214
00:17:54,608 --> 00:17:59,630
If I had just walked her home that night...

215
00:18:02,536 --> 00:18:05,254
this accident wouldn't have happened.

216
00:18:07,787 --> 00:18:10,746
I understand what you're saying,

217
00:18:11,239 --> 00:18:12,657
but I need to confirm it myself.

218
00:18:12,657 --> 00:18:14,441
Eun Sil.

219
00:18:16,332 --> 00:18:21,187
Don't you find all of this suspicious?

220
00:18:21,187 --> 00:18:24,880
That man, Gyosan, was there when your mother had her accident.

221
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:28,305
Do you think that's just a coincidence?

222
00:18:30,952 --> 00:18:33,898
 But what were you doing there last night? 

223
00:18:34,618 --> 00:18:37,199
 Didn't we part ways in front of Changdeok Palace? 

224
00:18:37,199 --> 00:18:41,285
 I was merely looking around the neighborhood... 

225
00:18:44,510 --> 00:18:46,402
What if he was involved in your mother's accident?

226
00:18:46,402 --> 00:18:48,311
That's enough!

227
00:18:49,863 --> 00:18:52,370
I don't want to hear it anymore.

228
00:18:56,947 --> 00:18:59,974
I have no idea what's going on.

229
00:19:01,419 --> 00:19:04,036
You must be confused.

230
00:19:04,036 --> 00:19:05,808
I understand.

231
00:19:06,415 --> 00:19:09,966
If you can't trust me...

232
00:19:10,789 --> 00:19:13,538
Then ask someone else.

233
00:19:13,538 --> 00:19:15,436
For example...

234
00:19:18,380 --> 00:19:21,277
The police.

235
00:19:21,277 --> 00:19:24,729
 Please leave a message after the beep— 

236
00:19:24,729 --> 00:19:27,706
It's the other lady again.

237
00:19:27,706 --> 00:19:29,859
She says the same thing every time!

238
00:19:35,421 --> 00:19:37,312
Young lady!

239
00:19:37,312 --> 00:19:40,610
Where have you been this late at night?

240
00:19:40,610 --> 00:19:42,657
Do you know how worried I was?

241
00:19:42,657 --> 00:19:45,131
You were worried about me?

242
00:19:45,131 --> 00:19:47,691
Of course I was.

243
00:19:48,969 --> 00:19:51,727
Why did you not answer your phone?

244
00:19:51,727 --> 00:19:54,736
You told me to always keep this with me, and pick up when you call.

245
00:19:54,736 --> 00:19:56,452
Mister.

246
00:19:57,747 --> 00:20:00,356
Are you hiding anything from me?

247
00:20:00,356 --> 00:20:03,405
What are you talking about all of a sudden?

248
00:20:03,405 --> 00:20:05,835
Something about my mother.

249
00:20:07,490 --> 00:20:11,470
Is there really nothing you need to tell me?

250
00:20:13,042 --> 00:20:18,059
 She is better off not knowing until I am certain. 

251
00:20:21,883 --> 00:20:23,682
No.

252
00:20:26,004 --> 00:20:28,590
The day my mom had her accident...

253
00:20:28,590 --> 00:20:31,388
Why were you there?

254
00:20:32,230 --> 00:20:33,800
That is...

255
00:20:34,380 --> 00:20:36,804
Give me an honest answer.

256
00:20:36,804 --> 00:20:40,194
Fine, I will tell you the truth.

257
00:20:40,194 --> 00:20:44,225
That night, I returned to that place because I was trying to go back to Joseon.

258
00:20:44,225 --> 00:20:48,215
Enough with that nonsense about Joseon!

259
00:20:49,147 --> 00:20:52,354
Give me something I can actually believe!

260
00:20:52,354 --> 00:20:53,611
Tell me why!

261
00:20:53,611 --> 00:20:56,381
Why were you there, at that time, at that exact place?

262
00:20:56,381 --> 00:20:58,717
Give me a reason that makes sense!

263
00:20:58,717 --> 00:21:01,492
Everything I have told you is the truth!

264
00:21:03,129 --> 00:21:05,221
Wait...

265
00:21:05,221 --> 00:21:07,260
Young lady,

266
00:21:08,183 --> 00:21:10,656
are you doubting me?

267
00:21:11,709 --> 00:21:14,398
I want to believe you.

268
00:21:15,340 --> 00:21:18,377
So give me an answer I can believe.

269
00:21:20,073 --> 00:21:25,103
If you refuse to accept the truth...

270
00:21:26,824 --> 00:21:29,631
then there is nothing more I can say.

271
00:21:46,390 --> 00:21:51,090
♫  On a day when the clouds fade away  ♫

272
00:21:52,730 --> 00:21:57,730
♫  A night I wish to fill completely, just as it is  ♫

273
00:21:57,730 --> 00:21:59,278
 Great! Isn't this fun? 

274
00:21:59,278 --> 00:22:02,420
 You need to match the line. 

