00:40:57,130 --> 00:41:02,120
♫  It was my first time feeling that way  ♫

540
00:41:02,120 --> 00:41:08,380
♫  The noisy moments came to a stop  ♫ 
 ♫  And I got to know you  ♫

541
00:41:08,380 --> 00:41:13,930
♫  The moment I wandered in a long dream  ♫

542
00:41:13,936 --> 00:41:15,340
 Did you sleep well? 

543
00:41:15,340 --> 00:41:22,220
♫  Even if everything flows away you are still by my side  ♫

544
00:41:22,220 --> 00:41:27,470
♫  Don't let go of my hand, not ever  ♫

545
00:41:28,270 --> 00:41:35,750
♫  When spring comes let's go there, together  ♫

546
00:41:35,790 --> 00:41:41,560
♫  Let's never be apart again  ♫

547
00:41:42,921 --> 00:41:45,557
Mister, sit here for a second.

548
00:41:57,948 --> 00:42:00,915
 - Why am I the only one having a hard time?  
 - Hilarious, right?

549
00:42:00,915 --> 00:42:04,892
Everyone laughs while watching my wooden acting.

550
00:42:08,100 --> 00:42:10,420
Come on, lighten up a little.

551
00:42:10,420 --> 00:42:13,600
Being gloomy doesn't suit you at all.

552
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:16,932
But what does wooden acting mean?

553
00:42:16,932 --> 00:42:20,931
Acting stiff like wood.

554
00:42:20,931 --> 00:42:23,494
It means my acting is terrible.

555
00:42:25,222 --> 00:42:28,828
I kept trying to become an actress,

556
00:42:28,828 --> 00:42:30,968
but I was always just a joke to people.

557
00:42:30,968 --> 00:42:34,294
I do not see what is so funny about this.

558
00:42:35,607 --> 00:42:38,985
Mocking you is not amusing at all.

559
00:42:38,985 --> 00:42:42,466
You really know how to say the right things, don't you?

560
00:42:43,955 --> 00:42:47,100
But they're right, my acting is wooden.

561
00:42:47,644 --> 00:42:51,230
I don't really understand what feeling sad really is.

562
00:42:51,775 --> 00:42:54,192
That's why I'll never make it as an actress.

563
00:42:54,792 --> 00:42:56,710
That is not true.

564
00:42:57,282 --> 00:43:00,203
You are a gifted artist, Mae Chang.

565
00:43:00,203 --> 00:43:04,180
The Mae Chang I knew was brilliant in poetry, in music,

566
00:43:04,180 --> 00:43:07,310
in every instrument.

567
00:43:07,315 --> 00:43:11,488
Was she really that incredible?

568
00:43:11,488 --> 00:43:13,120
Yes.

569
00:43:13,702 --> 00:43:17,843
I was a huge fan of her talent.

570
00:43:19,662 --> 00:43:22,362
Did she resemble me that much?

571
00:43:22,362 --> 00:43:25,544
You resemble her so much, it is almost as if you are the same person.

572
00:43:25,544 --> 00:43:28,630
That's not exactly common, you know?

573
00:43:28,630 --> 00:43:33,381
Anyway, my name is Jung Mi Sol.

574
00:43:33,912 --> 00:43:37,560
Jung Mi Sol doesn't have any of those talents.

575
00:43:37,560 --> 00:43:39,695
Take my word,

576
00:43:39,695 --> 00:43:41,500
Mae Chang.

577
00:43:41,500 --> 00:43:45,330
No, Jung Mi Sol...

578
00:43:45,330 --> 00:43:47,958
is a gifted artist.

579
00:44:18,864 --> 00:44:21,640
Even the most beautiful melodies...

580
00:44:22,599 --> 00:44:25,881
If no one hears them,

581
00:44:25,881 --> 00:44:30,773
they are no different from the fleeting whispers of the wind.

582
00:44:31,787 --> 00:44:33,726
My Lord, Gyosan.

583
00:44:41,611 --> 00:44:45,272
My Lady, terrible news!

584
00:44:53,240 --> 00:44:56,384
Stop! Stop!

585
00:44:56,384 --> 00:44:59,441
Please stop.

586
00:45:00,162 --> 00:45:03,210
I will confess everything!

587
00:45:03,210 --> 00:45:05,989
Please stop.

588
00:45:17,509 --> 00:45:21,832
So, do you finally remember?

589
00:45:24,196 --> 00:45:27,496
Do you recall the crime you and your men have committed?

590
00:45:28,731 --> 00:45:30,506
I...

591
00:45:31,929 --> 00:45:35,382
I have committed treason.

592
00:45:36,510 --> 00:45:39,136
I defied the King

593
00:45:39,136 --> 00:45:44,147
and I conspired to place Prince Yeongchang on the throne.

594
00:45:44,854 --> 00:45:47,693
I am guilty of high treason.

595
00:45:47,693 --> 00:45:50,104
So please.

596
00:45:50,104 --> 00:45:53,058
Just end my life.

597
00:45:55,759 --> 00:45:58,763
The criminal has confessed.

598
00:45:58,763 --> 00:46:01,519
For the crime of treason,

599
00:46:01,519 --> 00:46:04,185
he shall face the severest punishment.

600
00:46:07,345 --> 00:46:09,701
On the coming new moon...

601
00:46:12,147 --> 00:46:15,046
carry out their execution.

602
00:46:15,046 --> 00:46:16,886
 Yes, Your Excellency! 

603
00:46:27,875 --> 00:46:29,824
I have to go.

604
00:46:31,190 --> 00:46:33,115
Go where?

605
00:46:33,115 --> 00:46:35,170
Gwansong.

606
00:46:35,170 --> 00:46:39,508
No, Lee Hyuk is a dangerous man.

607
00:46:39,508 --> 00:46:42,530
I cannot let Lady Eun Sil stay by his side.

608
00:46:43,364 --> 00:46:46,401
She made her choice.

609
00:46:46,401 --> 00:46:49,594
It's her life. Let her deal with it.

610
00:46:49,594 --> 00:46:51,554
I have to go.

611
00:46:54,173 --> 00:46:56,220
You're not even in good shape.

612
00:46:56,220 --> 00:46:58,830
Rest today and go tomorrow.

613
00:46:58,838 --> 00:47:03,158
If I wait and something happens to her...

614
00:47:03,158 --> 00:47:05,990
I will not be able to live with myself.

615
00:47:05,990 --> 00:47:08,230
Thank you for everything.

616
00:47:10,286 --> 00:47:12,473
Fine.

617
00:47:12,473 --> 00:47:14,824
I'll take you there.

618
00:47:18,685 --> 00:47:20,619
Mom, I'm here.

619
00:47:22,410 --> 00:47:24,903
Chef Lee is here with me, too.

620
00:47:30,349 --> 00:47:34,389
I heard everything about Mr. Homeless.

621
00:47:37,477 --> 00:47:40,399
I can't believe I was so clueless…

622
00:47:40,399 --> 00:47:44,428
Thinking he was protecting our diner, I was grateful to him.

623
00:47:45,809 --> 00:47:48,013
I feel so stupid.

624
00:47:52,616 --> 00:47:55,300
But thanks to Chef Lee,

625
00:47:55,300 --> 00:47:58,717
at least I know the truth now.

626
00:47:58,717 --> 00:48:02,555
I kicked him out of the diner.

627
00:48:02,555 --> 00:48:07,325
And I'll make sure he pays for what he did to you.

628
00:48:11,642 --> 00:48:14,019
I'm going to talk to the nurse for a bit.

629
00:48:14,019 --> 00:48:17,282
That man might try to come see my mom again.

630
00:48:17,282 --> 00:48:20,135
So I need to warn them.

631
00:48:20,135 --> 00:48:23,723
Okay, I'll wait here.

632
00:48:23,723 --> 00:48:25,249
Okay.

633
00:48:27,178 --> 00:48:29,486
Mom, I'll be back.

634
00:48:41,196 --> 00:48:44,253
And you don't know where he went?

635
00:48:55,598 --> 00:48:57,102
Yes.

636
00:48:57,102 --> 00:48:58,898
I understand.

637
00:48:58,898 --> 00:49:00,598
Yes.

638
00:49:01,765 --> 00:49:04,040
Is she not at home?

639
00:49:04,040 --> 00:49:08,270
I called the restaurant, but they said Lee Hyuk is out.

640
00:49:08,270 --> 00:49:10,946
Looks like they went somewhere together.

641
00:49:14,545 --> 00:49:17,191
I hope nothing bad happens...

642
00:49:17,191 --> 00:49:18,740
Let's just go back, mister.

643
00:49:18,740 --> 00:49:20,940
We don't even know when they'll return.

644
00:49:22,388 --> 00:49:25,430
No, I have someone else I need to meet.

645
00:49:25,430 --> 00:49:27,570
You should head home, Mae Chang.

646
00:49:27,579 --> 00:49:29,296
Thank you.

647
00:49:31,780 --> 00:49:33,714
And for the clothes, too.

648
00:49:37,682 --> 00:49:39,720
   

649
00:49:39,720 --> 00:49:42,291
 Congratulations, inspector! 

650
00:50:00,670 --> 00:50:02,851
You there, officer!

651
00:50:02,851 --> 00:50:04,636
What?

652
00:50:05,794 --> 00:50:08,592
How did you know I was here?

653
00:50:08,592 --> 00:50:11,269
I come from the police station.

654
00:50:11,269 --> 00:50:14,223
They said you were in this area, so I searched everywhere.

655
00:50:16,562 --> 00:50:18,578
Let's talk outside.

656
00:50:19,185 --> 00:50:21,889
How is the investigation on Lee Hyuk going?

657
00:50:21,889 --> 00:50:24,027
You cannot afford to waste any more time.

658
00:50:24,027 --> 00:50:26,310
That man not only harmed the diner's madam,

659
00:50:26,310 --> 00:50:29,130
but now he is targeting Eun Sil!

660
00:50:29,135 --> 00:50:32,194
Why have I not heard any updates?

661
00:50:32,194 --> 00:50:34,515
Hey, Kang.

662
00:50:34,515 --> 00:50:36,631
What's going on?

663
00:50:36,631 --> 00:50:39,569
It's nothing.

664
00:50:40,775 --> 00:50:42,567
Follow me.

665
00:50:44,516 --> 00:50:45,794
Where are you going?

666
00:50:45,794 --> 00:50:47,612
Hey, officer!

667
00:50:48,360 --> 00:50:50,532
You're doing this to me on purpose, aren't you?

668
00:50:50,532 --> 00:50:54,940
You deliberately came to a police gathering to spout that nonsense, didn't you?

669
00:50:54,940 --> 00:50:58,872
I only spoke the truth, so why are you so upset?

670
00:50:59,885 --> 00:51:03,795
I've got enough on my plate as it is!

671
00:51:03,795 --> 00:51:05,989
I have made a formal request for an investigation.

672
00:51:05,989 --> 00:51:09,108
You need to reveal the truth about Lee Hyuk's crimes.

673
00:51:09,108 --> 00:51:12,213
- We have no time to lose. 
 - Reveal what, exactly?

674
00:51:12,213 --> 00:51:14,874
You are the suspect!

675
00:51:15,486 --> 00:51:16,657
What did you say?

676
00:51:16,657 --> 00:51:21,780
Bong Eun Sil thinks you were the one who hurt her mother!

677
00:51:21,780 --> 00:51:24,381
How would you know that?

678
00:51:24,381 --> 00:51:27,177
Because I'm the one who's supposed to arrest you.

679
00:51:27,177 --> 00:51:30,565
But if you go down, I go down with you.

680
00:51:32,272 --> 00:51:35,316
Ever since I helped you in the beginning, letting an unidentified person walk free

681
00:51:35,316 --> 00:51:37,413
and today's identification...

682
00:51:39,039 --> 00:51:40,883
Forget it.

683
00:51:40,883 --> 00:51:43,429
Can you please...

684
00:51:43,429 --> 00:51:46,120
just disappear?

685
00:51:46,120 --> 00:51:49,445
I'm begging you. Don't make things worse and just go.

686
00:51:49,445 --> 00:51:53,197
Lee Hyuk isn't someone you can take on.

687
00:51:53,197 --> 00:51:57,596
So you never planned to investigate Lee Hyuk at all, did you?

688
00:51:59,634 --> 00:52:02,818
How long have you been his lapdog?

689
00:52:03,708 --> 00:52:05,404
What?

690
00:52:05,404 --> 00:52:07,580
Lapdog?

691
00:52:07,580 --> 00:52:09,128
Say that again.

692
00:52:09,128 --> 00:52:10,760
Say that again!

693
00:52:10,760 --> 00:52:12,418
Move out of the way.

694
00:52:13,122 --> 00:52:16,779
I have nothing more to say to someone like you.

695
00:52:16,779 --> 00:52:19,310
I will find help elsewhere.

696
00:52:20,716 --> 00:52:24,618
I told you not to make things worse!

697
00:52:25,306 --> 00:52:26,336
I said, move!

698
00:52:26,336 --> 00:52:28,287
Why, you...

699
00:52:28,287 --> 00:52:29,779
What are you doing?

700
00:52:29,779 --> 00:52:31,632
I should have just...

701
00:52:32,719 --> 00:52:34,460
Let go of me!

702
00:52:35,143 --> 00:52:37,038
You bastard!

703
00:52:39,712 --> 00:52:43,959
Come on, why did you have to do that?

704
00:52:56,514 --> 00:52:58,805
 It is time to end this. 

705
00:53:06,087 --> 00:53:07,567
Hey.

706
00:53:07,567 --> 00:53:10,399
What's the matter?

707
00:53:10,399 --> 00:53:12,073
What?

708
00:53:12,823 --> 00:53:14,696
Kang!

709
00:53:24,201 --> 00:53:26,243
 My Lord, your friends are in danger. 

710
00:53:26,243 --> 00:53:29,340
 The seven illegitimate sons you cherish! They are in grave danger. 

711
00:53:29,340 --> 00:53:31,622
 My friends? In danger? 

712
00:53:31,622 --> 00:53:33,457
 It is my fault. 

713
00:53:33,457 --> 00:53:36,420
 I rejected his offer, and now my friends... 

714
00:53:36,420 --> 00:53:41,131
 I take it Gwansong was the one who ordered my death. 

715
00:53:43,872 --> 00:53:46,410
 Now, it is time to go. 

716
00:53:53,670 --> 00:54:00,540


717
00:54:03,650 --> 00:54:10,460
♫  Even if everything flows away you are still by my side  ♫

718
00:54:10,460 --> 00:54:16,570
♫  Don't let go of my hand, not ever  ♫

719
00:54:16,570 --> 00:54:23,800
♫  When spring comes let's go there, together  ♫

720
00:54:23,800 --> 00:54:30,700
♫  Let's never be apart again  ♫

721
00:54:44,360 --> 00:54:50,880
